abstract: Failing to reduce carbon pollution could cost the United States economy $150 billion a year, the Council of Economic Advisers said.
snippet: Failing to reduce carbon pollution could cost the United States economy $150 billion a year, the Council of Economic Advisers said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Failing to adequately reduce the carbon pollution that contributes to climate change could cost the United States economy $150 billion a year, according to an analysis by the White House Council of Economic Advisers released Tuesday.

lead_paragraph: 7 P.M. (BET) JUMPING THE BROOM (2011) Paula Patton and Laz Alonso play Sabrina Watson and Jason Taylor, lovebirds planning what should be the perfect wedding on Martha’s Vineyard. That is, until Jason’s mother (Loretta Devine), a postal worker with a chip on her shoulder, arrives from Brooklyn at the estate of Sabrina’s uptight parents. “Our family were never slaves,” says Mrs. Watson (Angela Bassett), who likes to converse in French. “We owned slaves.” Mayhem, of course, ensues as the film examines, among other subjects, class conflict among African-American families. Writing in The New York Times, A. O. Scott said that the film’s director, Salim Akil, and its screenwriters, Elizabeth Hunter and Arlene Gibbs, “fall back on the tried-and-true staple of the busy nuptial weekend to stage a talk show season’s worth of conflicts and revelations, both serious and comical.”

lead_paragraph: Sarah Patterson, a 27-year-old nurse, suffered four miscarriages over the last four years because of several medical problems, including a condition that causes cysts to form on the ovaries. After her second loss, she said, her husband asked for a divorce because he could not handle the stress.

abstract: After ordering the extradition to Germany of Johann Breyer, 89, who served as an armed guard at Auschwitz, a judge learned that the man had died hours earlier.
snippet: After ordering the extradition to Germany of Johann Breyer, 89, who served as an armed guard at Auschwitz, a judge learned that the man had died hours earlier.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In what will most likely be one of the last Nazi cases on American soil, an 89-year-old Philadelphia man who served as an armed guard at Auschwitz during World War II died Wednesday, just hours before a judge ordered him extradited to Germany in the murders of 216,000 prisoners at the notorious concentration camp.

abstract: Mr. Garner was best known as the amiable gambler Bret Maverick in the 1950s western “Maverick” and the cranky sleuth Jim Rockford in the 1970s series “The Rockford Files.”
snippet: Mr. Garner was best known as the amiable gambler Bret Maverick in the 1950s western “Maverick” and the cranky sleuth Jim Rockford in the 1970s series “The Rockford Files.”
lead_paragraph: James Garner, the wry and handsome leading man who slid seamlessly between television and the movies but was best known as the amiable gambler Bret Maverick in the 1950s western “Maverick” and the cranky sleuth Jim Rockford in the 1970s series “The Rockford Files,” died on Saturday night at his home in Los Angeles. He was 86.

snippet: Kyle Seager is the starting third baseman for the Seattle Mariners and his younger brothers, Corey and Justin, play in the minor leagues.
lead_paragraph: As the father of three competitive, athletic sons, Jeff Seager knows well the joys — and the perils — of raising a family around sports. Pickup games could be a problem.
